frameDefinitions: This frame describes a situation in which an Owner loses his or her Possession.
An Earner receives Earnings by providing Goods to a Buyer; providing the Goods also generally entails a cost, which may or may not be included in the consideration.
These are words describing situations in which a Perpetrator takes Goods from a  Victim or a Source.
This frame describes a Sufferer who experiences the loss of someone through death.
An Agent leaves behind a Theme effectively rendering it no longer within their control or of the normal security as one's property.
frameExamples: This reflects the 15 % jump in <t><fex name='Earnings'>earnings</fex></t> over 1994 .
I can't believe he <t>pickpocketed</t> my gold watch !
She <t>lost</t> her husband in the war.
Carolyn <t>abandoned</t> her car and jumped on a red double decker bus.
listRoleDefinitions: The original <fen>Owner</fen> of the <fen>Possession</fen>.
The object that is possessed by the <fen>Owner</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Possession</fen> is lost.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Possession</fen> is lost.
The <fen>Earner</fen> is involved in a transaction or set of transactions as the party that receives payment.
<fen>Earnings</fen> are the money given to the <fen>Earner</fen> in a transaction, generally in exchange for <fen>Goods</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
<fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) that takes the goods away.
<fen>Victim</fen> is the person (or other sentient being or group) that owns the goods before they are taken away by the perpetrator.
<fen>Goods</fen> is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be taken away.
<fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the goods, before they change location.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the theft occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the theft occurs.
The being or entity that emotionally experiences the death of the <fen>Deceased</fen>.
The entity that has died.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Deceased</fen> passed away.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Deceased</fen> passed away.
The <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex> is the person who acts to leave behind the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fex name='Theme'>Theme</fex> is the entity that is relinguished to no one from the <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex>'s possession.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
listRoleExamples: She made a lot of money <fex>in Africa</fex> .
Leslie stole the watch <fex>from the table</fex>.
Leslie STOLE the watch from Kim <fex>at dusk</fex>.
Leslie STOLE the watch from Kim <fex>in the park</fex>.
